---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Privacy Policy | Pace Insights',
  description: 'Learn about how Pace Insights collects, uses, and protects your personal data.',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 mx-auto lg:px-8 lg:py-20 max-w-4xl">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-10">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tighter tracking-tighter mb-4 font-heading">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          Last updated: April 8, 2025
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p>
          PACE INSIGHTS LIMITED ("we", "us", or "our") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you visit our website or use our services, in accordance with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and other applicable data protection laws.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          PACE INSIGHTS LIMITED<br>
          Company No: 06583092<br>
          VAT No: GB 933 6356 14<br>
          Registered Office: The Old Bakery, Camden Road, Tunbridge Wells, England, TN1 2QP
        </p>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this policy or your data, please contact us at: hello@paceinsights.com
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We may collect and process the following types of personal data:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Name and contact details (e.g. email address, phone number)</li>
          <li>Information you provide when filling out forms or surveys</li>
          <li>Technical and usage data (e.g. IP address, browser type, pages visited)</li>
          <li>Communication preferences and marketing consents</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How We Collect Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          We collect data through:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Direct interactions (e.g. when you contact us or subscribe to emails)</li>
          <li>Automated technologies (e.g. usage data captured via analytics tools)</li>
          <li>Third-party services integrated on our site</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          We use your personal data to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide and maintain our services</li>
          <li>Respond to your enquiries and provide support</li>
          <li>Send marketing emails or newsletters (if you've opted in)</li>
          <li>Improve our website, services, and user experience</li>
          <li>Ensure compliance with legal obligations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Our Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p>
          We rely on the following lawful bases:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Consent (for email marketing, optional forms)</li>
          <li>Legitimate interests (to improve our services, security, and communication)</li>
          <li>Legal obligations (to comply with applicable laws)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          We use trusted third-party service providers to help deliver and enhance our services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>ConvertKit</strong> – for managing our email communications and mailing list</li>
          <li><strong>Plausible Analytics</strong> – a privacy-friendly analytics tool that does not collect personal data or use cookies</li>
          <li><strong>OpenAI / OpenRouter</strong> – for powering interactive tools and assessments on our site. User input may be sent to these services for processing. We do not retain this data beyond the purpose of generating a response.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We ensure that any data shared with these providers is minimised and protected under appropriate agreements.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Your Data Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the following rights under UK GDPR:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>To access your personal data</li>
          <li>To correct or update inaccurate data</li>
          <li>To request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>To restrict or object to processing</li>
          <li>To withdraw consent at any time (where applicable)</li>
          <li>To lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes set out above, or as required to meet legal obligations.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We have implemented appropriate security measures to protect your data from loss, misuse, unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">International Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          If any personal data is transferred outside the UK or EEA, we ensure it is protected by appropriate safeguards, such as Standard Contractual Clauses.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Links to Other Websites</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may contain links to external websites not operated by us. We are not responsible for their privacy practices and encourage you to read their policies.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version will always be published on our website with the date of the last update.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions or to exercise your rights, please contact: hello@paceinsights.com
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            PACE INSIGHTS LIMITED<br>
            Company No: 06583092<br>
            VAT No: GB 933 6356 14<br>
            Registered Office: The Old Bakery, Camden Road, Tunbridge Wells, England, TN1 2QP
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
